translated: Dalgård, Johannes, principal, Oskarshamn, b. November 23, 1886 in Djura, Kopparberg. Married in 1930 to Anna Horn. Children: Ingemar b. 1931. Studied at the high school in Falun in 1907, received a Bachelor of Arts degree from Uppsala University in 1910, and completed a probationary year in teaching in 1916. Traveled to England and France in 1920, Germany, Italy, and Austria in 1921, Germany in 1923, Switzerland in 1924, Norway in 1925, France in 1926, Czechoslovakia, Italy, and Switzerland in 1927, Belgium, France, and Switzerland in 1930. Was a teacher in Bollnäs from 1912-1913, a substitute teacher in Sölvesborg from 1913-1914, a substitute clergyman in Ystad from 1914-1916, a regular teacher there in 1917, a substitute clergyman in 1918, in Skara from 1918-1919, a regular teacher in Örebro from 1919-1920, a substitute and assistant lecturer at Karlstad people's high school from 1920-1921, a clergyman in mathematics, physics, and chemistry at Oskarshamn secondary school in 1921, a substitute principal there in 1927 and 1929, and has been the principal since 1929. Was the principal's secretary from 1927-1929. Is a member of the city council since 1930, the planning committee since 1943, the police board, a member of the board of directors and vice-chairman of the people's school board, and the chairman of the lecture association. Has been awarded the Royal Order of the Seraphim in 1942.
